## The Database Error — What Happened & How to Fix It

**Error seen in server terminal:**
```
pymongo.errors.ServerSelectionTimeoutError: localhost:27017: [Errno 61] Connection refused
```

**Plain English:** The backend server started fine, but when the frontend asked for `/api/sales` and `/api/recipes`, the backend tried to connect to MongoDB and found nothing listening on port 27017 — because **MongoDB was not running**.

**The fix:** Start MongoDB before starting the backend (see step 1 above).

The server code itself has no bug. Every 500 error in that log has the same single root cause: MongoDB was off.

**To confirm MongoDB is running on Mac:**
```bash
brew services list | grep mongodb
```
It should say `started`. If it says `stopped`, run `brew services start mongodb-community`.

---

## Verification

After starting all three (MongoDB → backend → frontend):
1. Open `http://localhost:3000` — the Dashboard should load with sales data
2. Open `http://localhost:8002/docs` — Swagger API docs should appear
3. No 500 errors should appear in the backend terminal

